Niger State House of Assembly has passed into law 2020 appropriation law of N155. 45 billion. The budget was passed with an increase over what was presented by Governor Abubakar Sani Belllo. The House unanimously passed the budget after the chairman of the Appropriation Committee, Him Mohammed Bashir Lokogoma presented the report of the committee to plenary yesterday in Minna. The committee chairman stated that the increase in the budget was as a result of some statutory spending and funding earlier omitted during presentation to the House. The budget therefore showed an increase of N7. 24 billion over N148. 21 billion budget submitted to the House earlier by the governor. Lokogoma said the budget is made up of N70 billion recurrent expenditure  and N85. 4 billion capital expenditure as against N69.8billion recurrent expenditure and N78.2billion capital expenditure submitted by the governor respectively. After deliberations on the presentation by the chairman of Appropriation Committee, the deputy speaker asked for the House’s approval, which was unanimously granted. The deputy speaker thereafter instructed the clerk of the House, Alhaji Abdullah  Kalgara to produce a clean copy for the governor’s assent.